Author: MORRIS
Vol / Page: 264
Edition:
Quote: ~ (pronounced leed), a mining term. In the Western United  States and elsewhere, the term leadin mining is used as  equivalent for lode. In Australia, the word leadis only used in reference to alluvial mining, and signifies the old river-bed in which gold is found. [1875]
